Example: Using PBMM to Analyze Public Figures

This document demonstrates how Priority-Based Mindset Mapping can be applied to public figures.

The objective is not to diagnose their private psychology or claim privileged knowledge of their intentions. Public-figure analysis is necessarily based on an incomplete sample:

public statements,
recurring behavior,
professional decisions,
self-presentation,
reported interactions,
and the roles they repeatedly occupy.

The resulting map therefore describes a person’s observable public mask, not their entire identity.

The analysis method

A PBMM analysis proceeds through five questions:

Which priorities repeatedly appear in the person’s public behavior?
Which priorities are they willing to sacrifice when priorities conflict?
What is their strongest masculine priority: dignity, security, or acquisition?
What is their strongest feminine priority: recognition, harmony, or comfort?
Which of those two priorities appears to govern the relationship?

The dominant masculine and feminine priorities identify the archetypal pairing. Their direction identifies the archetype.

The remaining four priorities act as modifiers.

Exact numerical weights are unnecessary for this human-scale application. Terms such as dominant, high, moderate, and subordinate are sufficient to produce a useful provisional map.

Donald Trump
Evidence base

Donald Trump is serving as the 47th president of the United States in 2026. His administration publicly foregrounds border control, economic growth, national security, and American energy production. The White House’s celebration of the nation’s 250th anniversary also places heavy emphasis on American independence, greatness, and historical achievement.

His recent public behavior has continued to favor direct confrontation, leverage, visible victory, and personal intervention. In July 2026, Reuters reported his confrontational positions involving NATO spending, Spain, Greenland, Iran, and even a dispute involving the U.S. national soccer team.

Priority map
Priority	Estimated public weight
Dignity	Dominant
Recognition	Very high
Security	High
Acquisition	High
Harmony	Conditional
Comfort	Subordinate
Central pairing

Dignity governing recognition

Archetype
The King

The King establishes value, sovereignty, standards, and authority, then expects those things to be acknowledged.

Trump’s public rhetoric repeatedly frames events through questions of standing:

Is America being respected?
Is someone taking advantage of the country?
Does an adversary believe the United States is weak?
Has Trump’s own contribution been properly acknowledged?
Does an agreement look like a victory or a concession?

Recognition is extremely important, but it appears to orbit dignity. Praise, attention, visible credit, ceremony, and demonstrations of loyalty confirm rightful standing. Failure to recognize that standing can be interpreted as disrespect.

Security and acquisition are also prominent. Strong borders, military deterrence, economic leverage, energy production, trade concessions, and territorial influence all occupy important places in his public program. But they are frequently narrated through dignity:

America must possess strength because America must not be humiliated, exploited, or treated as subordinate.

What the King mask notices

The King is highly sensitive to:

status,
loyalty,
public acknowledgment,
challenges to authority,
national or personal humiliation,
and whether an outcome can be presented as victory.

It is less naturally attentive to harmony for its own sake. Harmony is welcomed when it reflects unity around recognized leadership. It is readily sacrificed when compromise appears to require submission.

Predictive hypotheses

This map would predict that Trump will generally:

respond strongly to public disrespect,
prefer proposals that visibly confirm American or personal strength,
remain more flexible when given acknowledgment and room to claim victory,
sacrifice diplomatic harmony before sacrificing dignity,
and describe acquisitions, concessions, or leverage as evidence of restored standing.
Alternative interpretation

Trump could be mapped as a Champion if security and public proof of strength were judged more fundamental than dignity. The King reading is stronger because questions of respect, recognition, authority, and victory appear to organize even his security and acquisition policies.

Keanu Reeves
Evidence base

Keanu Reeves’ recent public activity combines acting, music, publishing, motorcycles, business, and collaborative creative work. In discussing the 2026 documentary series about ARCH Motorcycle’s racing project, Reeves emphasized teamwork, shared emotion, resilience, building, and the human experience behind competition.

His professional advice has similarly emphasized respecting colleagues and avoiding egotistical behavior. Accounts of his relationship and creative partnership with Alexandra Grant repeatedly emphasize mutual respect, play, independence, and collaboration.

Priority map
Priority	Estimated public weight
Harmony	Dominant
Dignity	Very high
Acquisition	Moderate to high
Comfort	Moderate
Security	Moderate
Recognition	Subordinate
Central pairing

Dignity governing harmony

Archetype
The Gentleman

The Gentleman preserves relationship, courtesy, and cooperation without surrendering dignity.

Reeves’ public mask does not appear organized around being admired, dominant, or visibly superior. Recognition accompanies his work, but he rarely appears to make acknowledgment the center of his public presentation.

His harmony is also not simple agreeableness. It is supported by dignity:

respect for collaborators,
respect for craft,
personal privacy,
restraint,
and an apparent unwillingness to turn every interaction into a contest for status.

The Gentleman seeks a social field in which people can cooperate without degrading themselves or one another.

What the Gentleman mask notices

The Gentleman is sensitive to:

mutual respect,
professionalism,
needless ego,
the dignity of collaborators,
fair participation,
and whether people are being treated as human beings rather than instruments.

Harmony is important, but dignity gives it boundaries. This distinguishes the Gentleman from a configuration that preserves peace through appeasement.

Acquisition remains meaningful. Reeves continues entering new creative and commercial fields, including motorcycles, music, books, and film. But acquisition appears to occur through participation and craft rather than domination.

Predictive hypotheses

This map would predict that Reeves will generally:

prefer collaborative rather than hierarchical creative environments,
avoid unnecessary public status contests,
accept recognition without making it the governing purpose,
tolerate difficulty when it serves craft or shared creation,
and withdraw or establish boundaries rather than publicly humiliate an opponent.
Alternative interpretation

Reeves could be mapped as harmony governing dignity, producing the Lady archetype in PBMM’s symbolic language. The Gentleman interpretation is stronger because his relational orientation appears anchored in self-possession and mutual respect rather than in preserving social ease at any cost.

Martha Stewart
Evidence base

Martha Stewart’s public work is centered on making ordinary life more functional, cultivated, reliable, and enjoyable. Her 2026 book, The Martha Way, organizes home and lifestyle mastery around cooking, entertaining, home organization, collecting, and gardening. Its stated approach combines aspirational outcomes with foundational lessons and repeatable procedures.

Her larger career converted domestic knowledge, presentation, organization, and personal standards into a highly recognizable commercial identity. Stewart has described herself as her own ideal customer, reader, and student, while emphasizing her ability to anticipate what her audience wants.

Priority map
Priority	Estimated public weight
Comfort	Dominant feminine priority
Security	Dominant masculine priority
Dignity	High
Acquisition	High
Recognition	High
Harmony	Moderate
Central pairing

Security governing comfort

Archetype
The Steward

The Steward preserves, organizes, and maintains the systems that make comfort dependable.

Stewart’s public project is not merely producing pleasant experiences. It involves mastery over the conditions that generate them:

correct methods,
reliable routines,
organized spaces,
cultivated land,
maintained tools,
preserved resources,
repeatable standards,
and detailed practical knowledge.

Comfort is the visible product. Security supplies the structure beneath it.

The Steward does not merely enjoy the harvest. The Steward knows how the garden was planted, how the pantry was organized, how the table was prepared, and how the entire process can be repeated correctly.

What the Steward mask notices

The Steward is highly attentive to:

disorder,
waste,
unreliable methods,
neglected maintenance,
poor preparation,
declining standards,
and the relationship between present discipline and future livability.

Stewart also displays strong dignity and acquisition. Her public identity is highly self-authored, and she has repeatedly transformed practical knowledge into publishing, broadcasting, products, and commercial capability.

That gives her Steward mask a strong secondary Matriarch quality. She does not merely maintain a system. She establishes authority through command of the cultivated domain.

Predictive hypotheses

This map would predict that Stewart will generally:

respond to disorder by creating procedures,
prefer reliable methods over vague inspiration,
convert knowledge into reusable systems and products,
evaluate beauty partly through function and maintenance,
resist dependence on people who cannot meet established standards,
and treat comfort as something constructed through competence rather than passively consumed.
Alternative interpretation

Stewart could be classified as a Hearthkeeper if comfort were judged to govern security. That archetype protects familiarity and restoration from disruption.

The Steward interpretation is stronger because Stewart’s public work emphasizes mastery, repeatability, management, and disciplined control of the conditions that produce comfort. Her orientation is not simply preserving a cozy center. It is engineering one.

Comparative map
Public figure	Dominant masculine priority	Dominant feminine priority	Governing direction	Archetype
Donald Trump	Dignity	Recognition	Dignity governs recognition	King
Keanu Reeves	Dignity	Harmony	Dignity governs harmony	Gentleman
Martha Stewart	Security	Comfort	Security governs comfort	Steward

The comparison is useful because these three people all display discipline, success, public visibility, and considerable personal agency. Conventional descriptions might place all three under vague labels such as ambitious, confident, hardworking, or influential.

PBMM distinguishes the motivational organization beneath those similarities.

Trump’s public mask asks:

Is my authority and value being acknowledged?

Reeves’ public mask asks:

Can dignity and relationship coexist without unnecessary ego?

Stewart’s public mask asks:

Are the systems in place to make life function beautifully and reliably?

These different geometries create different strengths, sensitivities, communication styles, and predictable tradeoffs.

What this exercise demonstrates

PBMM does not merely attach an archetype to a person. A responsible analysis moves through a sequence:

Evidence → priority weighting → dominant pairing → governing direction → archetypal mask → tentative predictions

The model becomes useful when it predicts what a person is likely to notice or sacrifice.

The King may sacrifice harmony before dignity.

The Gentleman may sacrifice recognition before mutual respect.

The Steward may sacrifice spontaneity before reliability.

These are not certainties. They are testable expectations generated by the model.

Limits of public-figure analysis

Public figures are especially difficult to map because their visible behavior is shaped by:

public relations,
commercial branding,
institutional roles,
selective media coverage,
strategic performance,
and limited access to private life.

An archetype assigned through public evidence should therefore be understood as:

The recurring mask presented through the available evidence.

It should not be treated as proof of private motives, moral character, mental health, or inevitable future behavior.

The map remains provisional. New evidence may alter the weighting, reveal another governing configuration, or show that the apparent archetype was partly a product of the public role.

The purpose is not to place famous people into boxes.

The purpose is to demonstrate how a small priority matrix can produce coherent, comparable, and potentially predictive interpretations of very different public personalities.
